      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GINA GULLA (4) scored well last start as odds-on favourite by 3 lengths at this track in a handy 34.99 beating Gigglin'. Has a tricky draw to overcome but has a good record over this journey. Has never missed the frame from five starts from this draw, including three wins. Hard to fault his form and he makes plenty of appeal. DAINTREE SNIPER (8) is having his first look at this course. In the money last start when third (30.21) at Murray Bridge over 530m. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from four starts. Expected to feature again. CARE FACTOR (2) stalked the lead from a middle draw and boxed on well to finish 3 lengths back in third (31.12) at this track in a Invitation over 530m. Winning chance. EL REY (1) did a good job to finish second last time out over 530m at this track (31.23) in a Grade 5/6, the second top-three finish on the trot.",
